Key roads will be closed today ahead of Mashujaa Day celebrations to be held in Mwea, Kirinyaga County.  Speaking during a media breakfast meeting in Mwea yesterday, Central Regional Commissioner Wilfred Nyagwanga said the main Nairobi-Nyeri road will be closed at Makutano. He advised motorists to use the Nairobi-Mwea-Embu-Meru and divert to the Sagana-Nyeri road.  He also advised motorists using the Embu-Kutus-Kerugoya road to take alternative routes at Samson Corner.  "Motorists using the Nairobi-Embu-Meru are advised to use Makutano-Sagana-Nyeri route," he said.  Nyagwanga called for patience and cooperation from motorists.  Former Mwea MP recalls birth and rise of Ngurubani town  As we celebrate achievers, we should name and shame the looters  Rise and rise of town that will host this year's Mashujaa fete  Rampant corruption mocks our Mashujaas sacrifices He told miraa drivers to be disciplined while using alternative roads. The roads will be closed at 5am while the stadium will be opened at 4am.        REGGAE IS BACK: The final BBI report unveiled in Kisii and received by President Uhuru and Raila  Government launches Huduma Namba Card as Kenya marks Mashujaa day today  Celebrating Mashujaa: The National Celebrations held in Kisii County By Wainaina Ndung’u | 6 hours ago By Muriithi Mugo | 6 hours ago By Timothy Kariuki | 6 hours ago By Fidelis Kabunyi | 16 hours ago